theme_viny_bright <- function(){
  
  library(ggthemes)
  
  ggthemes::theme_fivethirtyeight() %+replace%
  
  theme(
    axis.title = element_text(),
    
    axis.text = element_text(size = 13),
    
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
    
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    
    legend.background = element_rect(fill = NA),
    
    legend.key = element_rect(fill = NA),

    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                              size = 19,
                              face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, colour = "maroon")
      )
  
  }

theme_set(theme_viny_bright())

top_freq_elements <- function(x, n =5){
  table(x) %>% 
    as.data.frame() %>% 
    top_n(n, Freq) %>%   # Freq col comes from above dataframe naming
    arrange(desc(Freq))
}

Gender Bar plot

bar plot

customer_data %>% 
  mutate(bins = cut_width(Age, 10)) %>% 
  group_by(bins, Gender) %>% 
  tally() %>% 
  mutate(n = as.numeric(n)) %>% # without this line it was giving error
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(gender_count2 = case_when(Gender == "Female" ~ n * -1,
                                   TRUE ~ n)) %>%
  
  ggplot(aes(x = as.factor(bins), y = gender_count2, fill = Gender)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.52) +
  theme_classic() +
  geom_text(aes(label = n,y = gender_count2 + sign(gender_count2) * 2),
            col = "black", size = 3) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("darkblue","maroon")) +
  labs(title = "Age / gender distribution" ) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 15), 
        axis.title = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(), 
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 11), 
        axis.line = element_blank()
  )

Function bar plot

library(glue)
bar_bifactor_stack_plot <- function(df, bin_var, bin_width = 10, factor_var) {

  df %>% 
  mutate(bins = cut_width({{bin_var}}, bin_width)) %>%
  
  group_by(bins, {{factor_var}}) %>%
  tally() %>%
  mutate(n = as.numeric(n)) %>% # without this line it was giving error
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(gender_count2 = case_when({{factor_var}} == "Female" ~ n * -1,
                                   TRUE ~ n)) %>%
  
  ggplot(aes(x = as.factor(bins), y = gender_count2, fill = {{factor_var}})) +
  geom_col(width = 0.52) +
  theme_classic() +
  geom_text(aes(label = n,y = gender_count2 + sign(gender_count2) * 2),
            col = "black", size = 3) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("darkblue","maroon")) +
  labs(
       x = glue("{quo_name(enquo(bin_var))} bins"),
       y = glue("{quo_name(enquo(factor_var))} count"),
       title = glue("{quo_name(enquo(bin_var))} / {quo_name(enquo(factor_var))} distribution")
       ) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 15),
        # axis.title = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 11),
        axis.line = element_blank()
  )
  
  }
bar_bifactor_stack_plot(df = customer_data, bin_var = Age, bin_width = 15, factor_var = Gender)

library(factoextra)
library(tidymodels)

data prep

customer_data %>% head()
rownames(customer_data) <- customer_data$CustomerID  

head(customer_data)
cust_rec <- recipe(~ ., data = customer_data) %>% 
  step_rm(contains("CustomerID")) %>% 
  step_normalize(all_numeric()) %>% 
  step_range(all_numeric()) %>% 
  step_dummy(all_nominal()) %>% 
  prep()
  
cust_rec
Data Recipe

Inputs:

Training data contained 200 data points and no missing data.

Operations:

Variables removed CustomerID [trained]
Centering and scaling for Age, Annual.Income..k.., Spending.Score..1.100. [trained]
Range scaling to [0,1] for Age, Annual.Income..k.., Spending.Score..1.100. [trained]
Dummy variables from Gender [trained]
preprocessed_cust <- juice(cust_rec)
